Kassie DePaiva, a well-known Soap Opera Actress hailing from Kentucky, has amassed a remarkable net worth of $4 million as estimated for the year 2024. With her exceptional talent and captivating performances, DePaiva has cemented her name in the world of soap operas. Throughout her career, she has portrayed numerous beloved characters and garnered a devoted fanbase. Her consistent success and hard work have greatly contributed to her significant net worth, reflecting both her talent and dedication to her craft.

Some Kassie DePaiva images

About

Actress who became known for portraying Blair Cramer on the soap opera One Life to Live.

Before Fame

She attended Indiana University and UCLA.

Trivia

She made her television debut in 1986, playing Chelsea Reardon on the soap opera Guiding Light.

Family Life

She married James DePaiva in 1996, and the couple welcomed a son, James Quentin, in 1997.

Associated With

She has appeared on One Life to Live, just like Robin Strasser.
